{%- comment -%}
  vf-footer.liquid

  NEW SECTION — sections/vf-footer.liquid.
  Do NOT modify Dawn's native footer.liquid. The merchant places this
  section in their sections/footer.json group via the theme customiser.
  Root element is <section class="vf-footer">, not <footer>.

  Three regions: newsletter strip / link columns / bottom bar.
  All three are hairline-divided.

  Schema contract: docs/section-schemas.md §7
  Visual reference: ui_kits/website/Footer.jsx

  Judgement calls
  ───────────────
  1.  Newsletter form uses {%- form 'customer' -%} (Shopify native), not
      plain <form action="/contact">. Handles posted_successfully? and
      errors automatically.

  2.  Submit button is <button type="submit">, not vf-button snippet.
      The vf-button snippet renders <a>, which cannot submit a form.
      .vf-footer__submit in this section's {% style %} block mirrors the
      ghost aesthetic (transparent, --vf-border-1, Bone text, Bone-bright
      hover). Form-submit exception — not a re-implementation.

  3.  Column title colour: JSX colTitle uses #C9A96E (Gold) — JSX DRIFT.
      Corrected to --vf-fg-3. Gold is reserved for Série II / certificate
      moments. Footer logo is a locked SVG asset — Gold: zero references
      anywhere in this section.

  4.  Subscribe button colour: JSX has raw <button style={{ color: "#C9A96E" }}>
      — JSX DRIFT. Corrected to ghost (Bone text / Bone-bright hover).
      Filled Teal not used here — the newsletter strip already carries a
      Teal eyebrow moment; two competing Teal accents in the same region is
      wrong. Ghost is the correct footer register.

  5.  BĒHANCE → BEHANCE. Macron not in approved glyph list (CLAUDE.md §3);
      Behance brand uses a plain E.

  6.  Studio description max-width: 280px — deliberate typographic measure
      literal matching JSX. Same category as Material's 460px.

  7.  Logo: shopify_logo.svg asset at 128×32 (height 32px, width auto via
      CSS). Replaces the original span-based wordmark. SVG aspect ratio 4:1.
      32px is lighter than the 40px header logo — correct footer register.
      .vf-wordmark__* classes in vf-tokens.css are preserved as orphaned
      tokens — reserved for potential future packaging or certificate surfaces.

  8.  Column title tracking: 0.28em (--vf-track-eyebrow). JSX uses 0.30em.
      Delta is 0.02em — sub-perceptual. Token wins.

  9.  Column title font-size: 9px — navigation label chrome. Same register
      as Atelier metric labels and Material FIG. caption. CLAUDE.md 11px
      floor applies to body copy; not escalated.

 10.  Link line-height: 2.2 — deliberate literal. No token exists in this
      range. Controls click-target spacing between links, not text
      readability. Matches JSX exactly.

 11.  Studio description, EST. 2026 line, newsletter sub-line are all
      hardcoded brand-identity statements. Not merchant-editable per
      schema contract. EST year is 2026 (studio founding year).

 12.  Schema doc §7 says "Wordmark in bottom band" — JSX places the
      wordmark in the wide studio column (Region 2). JSX is the visual
      contract; schema doc needs a correction commit.

 13.  Three-breakpoint strategy: default single-column / 750–959px (studio
      full-width above 2×2 link grid) / 960px+ (full 1.4fr 1fr×4). Studio
      column uses grid-column: 1 / -1 at tablet — no wrapper div needed.
      Tablet break is genuine: five 1fr columns at 800–1000px viewport
      renders each column at ~130px — unreadable without it.

 14.  Social ↗ glyph injected via ::after — approved unicode glyph
      per CLAUDE.md §3. Not in merchant content.

 15.  Social link hover: .vf-footer__social-link .vf-mono { color: inherit }
      lets the anchor's own transition drive the colour change, avoiding a
      direct class override on vf-mono's internal colour rule.

 16.  enabled_on omitted — section available everywhere. Merchant assigns
      it to footer.json via the theme customiser.
{%- endcomment -%}

<section
  class="vf-footer"
  data-section-id="{{ section.id }}"
>

  {%- comment -%}── Region 1 · Newsletter strip ──{%- endcomment -%}
  <div class="vf-footer__newsletter">
    <div class="vf-footer__newsletter-inner">

      <div class="vf-footer__newsletter-left">
        {%- render 'vf-eyebrow', text: 'Studio Dispatch' -%}
        <h3 class="vf-footer__newsletter-headline">
          {{- section.settings.newsletter_headline_part_1 | escape -}}<br>
          <em>{{- section.settings.newsletter_headline_part_2 | escape -}}</em>
        </h3>
        {%- if section.settings.newsletter_body != blank -%}
          <div class="vf-footer__newsletter-body">
            {{- section.settings.newsletter_body -}}
          </div>
        {%- endif -%}
      </div>

      <div class="vf-footer__newsletter-right">
        {%- form 'customer', id: 'ContactFooter', class: 'vf-footer__newsletter-form' -%}
          <input type="hidden" name="contact[tags]" value="newsletter">
          <div class="vf-footer__email-row">
            <label class="visually-hidden" for="NewsletterEmail">Email address</label>
            <input
              type="email"
              name="contact[email]"
              id="NewsletterEmail"
              class="vf-footer__email-input"
              placeholder="you@studio.com"
              autocomplete="email"
              required
            >
            <button type="submit" class="vf-footer__submit">
              {{- section.settings.newsletter_cta_label | escape -}}
            </button>
          </div>
          {%- comment -%}Sub-line: hardcoded operational copy. Not merchant-editable.{%- endcomment -%}
          {%- render 'vf-mono', text: 'Four notes a year. No promotions. Unsubscribe in one click.', size: 'small', color: 'fg-3' -%}
          {%- if form.posted_successfully? -%}
            <p class="vf-footer__newsletter-success">Subscribed.</p>
          {%- elsif form.errors -%}
            <p class="vf-footer__newsletter-error">{{ form.errors | default_errors }}</p>
          {%- endif -%}
        {%- endform -%}
      </div>

    </div>
  </div>

  {%- comment -%}── Region 2 · Link columns ──{%- endcomment -%}
  <div class="vf-footer__columns">
    <div class="vf-footer__columns-inner">

      {%- comment -%}Studio column — hardcoded brand identity. Not merchant-editable.{%- endcomment -%}
      <div class="vf-footer__studio">
        <img
          src="{{ 'shopify_logo.svg' | asset_url }}"
          alt="Voxel Forge"
          class="vf-footer__logo"
          width="128"
          height="32"
          loading="lazy"
        >
        <p class="vf-footer__studio-desc">Voxel Forge is a Chennai studio producing precision 3D-printed sculptural lighting in numbered editions.</p>
        {%- render 'vf-mono', text: 'EST. 2026 · CHENNAI · INDIA', size: 'small', color: 'fg-3' -%}
      </div>

      {%- for block in section.blocks -%}
        {%- if block.type == 'link_column' -%}
          <div class="vf-footer__col" {{ block.shopify_attributes }}>
            {%- if block.settings.title != blank -%}
              <div class="vf-footer__col-title">{{- block.settings.title | escape -}}</div>
            {%- endif -%}
            <ul class="vf-footer__col-links">
              {%- if block.settings.link_1_label != blank -%}
                <li><a class="vf-footer__link" href="{{ block.settings.link_1_url }}">{{- block.settings.link_1_label | escape -}}</a></li>
              {%- endif -%}
              {%- if block.settings.link_2_label != blank -%}
                <li><a class="vf-footer__link" href="{{ block.settings.link_2_url }}">{{- block.settings.link_2_label | escape -}}</a></li>
              {%- endif -%}
              {%- if block.settings.link_3_label != blank -%}
                <li><a class="vf-footer__link" href="{{ block.settings.link_3_url }}">{{- block.settings.link_3_label | escape -}}</a></li>
              {%- endif -%}
              {%- if block.settings.link_4_label != blank -%}
                <li><a class="vf-footer__link" href="{{ block.settings.link_4_url }}">{{- block.settings.link_4_label | escape -}}</a></li>
              {%- endif -%}
            </ul>
          </div>
        {%- endif -%}
      {%- endfor -%}

    </div>
  </div>

  {%- comment -%}── Region 3 · Bottom bar ──{%- endcomment -%}
  <div class="vf-footer__bottom">
    <div class="vf-footer__bottom-inner">
      {%- render 'vf-mono', text: section.settings.bottom_bar_text, size: 'small', color: 'fg-3' -%}
      {%- assign has_social_blocks = false -%}
      {%- for block in section.blocks -%}
        {%- if block.type == 'social_link' -%}
          {%- assign has_social_blocks = true -%}
          {%- break -%}
        {%- endif -%}
      {%- endfor -%}
      {%- if has_social_blocks -%}
        <div class="vf-footer__social">
          {%- for block in section.blocks -%}
            {%- if block.type == 'social_link' -%}
              <a
                class="vf-footer__social-link"
                href="{{ block.settings.url }}"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener"
                {{ block.shopify_attributes }}
              >
                {%- render 'vf-mono', text: block.settings.label, size: 'small', color: 'fg-3' -%}
              </a>
            {%- endif -%}
          {%- endfor -%}
        </div>
      {%- endif -%}
    </div>
  </div>

</section>

{% style %}
  /* ── Section root ── */
  .vf-footer {
    background: var(--vf-obsidian);
    border-top: var(--vf-hairline) solid var(--vf-border-2);
  }

  /* ── Region 1 · Newsletter strip ── */
  .vf-footer__newsletter {
    padding: var(--vf-s-8) var(--vf-grid-margin-d);
    border-bottom: var(--vf-hairline) solid var(--vf-border-2);
  }

  .vf-footer__newsletter-inner {
    max-width: var(--vf-grid-max);
    margin: 0 auto;
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: var(--vf-s-6);
    align-items: center;
  }

  @media screen and (min-width: 750px) {
    .vf-footer__newsletter-inner {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
      gap: var(--vf-s-8);
    }
  }

  .vf-footer__newsletter-left {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--vf-s-4);
  }

  .vf-footer__newsletter-headline {
    font-family: var(--vf-ff-display);
    font-weight: var(--vf-w-light);
    font-size: var(--vf-fs-h2);
    line-height: var(--vf-lh-h);
    letter-spacing: var(--vf-track-tight);
    color: var(--vf-fg-1);
    margin: 0;
  }

  .vf-footer__newsletter-headline em {
    color: var(--vf-fg-3);
    font-style: italic;
  }

  .vf-footer__newsletter-body {
    font-family: var(--vf-ff-body);
    font-weight: var(--vf-w-light);
    font-size: var(--vf-fs-body);
    line-height: var(--vf-lh-body);
    color: var(--vf-fg-2);
  }

  .vf-footer__newsletter-body p { margin: 0 0 var(--vf-s-2); }
  .vf-footer__newsletter-body p:last-child { margin-bottom: 0; }

  /* ── Newsletter form ── */
  .vf-footer__newsletter-right {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--vf-s-3);
  }

  .vf-footer__email-row {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: var(--vf-s-3);
    padding-bottom: var(--vf-s-2);
    border-bottom: var(--vf-hairline) solid var(--vf-border-1);
  }

  .vf-footer__email-input {
    flex: 1;
    min-width: 0;
    background: transparent;
    border: none;
    color: var(--vf-fg-1);
    font-family: var(--vf-ff-body);
    font-size: var(--vf-fs-body);
    font-weight: var(--vf-w-light);
    outline: none;
    padding: 0;
  }

  .vf-footer__email-input::placeholder {
    color: var(--vf-fg-3);
  }

  /* Form submit — ghost aesthetic. vf-button snippet outputs <a>; cannot be
     used for type="submit". Section-scoped rule is the accepted exception. */
  .vf-footer__submit {
    display: inline-flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    min-height: var(--vf-hit-min);
    padding: 0 var(--vf-s-4);
    font-family: var(--vf-ff-body);
    font-size: var(--vf-fs-label);
    font-weight: var(--vf-w-light);
    letter-spacing: var(--vf-track-label);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--vf-fg-2);
    background: transparent;
    border: var(--vf-hairline) solid var(--vf-border-1);
    border-radius: var(--vf-radius-0);
    cursor: pointer;
    white-space: nowrap;
    transition:
      color        var(--vf-dur-base) var(--vf-ease),
      border-color var(--vf-dur-base) var(--vf-ease);
  }

  .vf-footer__submit:hover {
    color: var(--vf-fg-1);
    border-color: var(--vf-fg-1);
  }

  .vf-footer__newsletter-success {
    font-family: var(--vf-ff-body);
    font-size: var(--vf-fs-body);
    font-weight: var(--vf-w-light);
    color: var(--vf-signal-success);
    margin: 0;
  }

  .vf-footer__newsletter-error {
    font-family: var(--vf-ff-body);
    font-size: var(--vf-fs-body);
    font-weight: var(--vf-w-light);
    color: var(--vf-signal-error);
    margin: 0;
  }

  /* ── Region 2 · Link columns ── */
  .vf-footer__columns {
    padding: var(--vf-s-8) var(--vf-grid-margin-d);
  }

  .vf-footer__columns-inner {
    max-width: var(--vf-grid-max);
    margin: 0 auto;
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    gap: var(--vf-s-5);
    align-items: start;
  }

  @media screen and (min-width: 750px) {
    .vf-footer__columns-inner {
      grid-template-columns: repeat(2, 1fr);
    }
    /* Studio col spans full row; 4 link cols flow as 2×2 below. */
    .vf-footer__studio {
      grid-column: 1 / -1;
    }
  }

  @media screen and (min-width: 960px) {
    .vf-footer__columns-inner {
      grid-template-columns: 1.4fr 1fr 1fr 1fr 1fr;
      gap: var(--vf-s-6);
    }
    .vf-footer__studio {
      grid-column: auto;
    }
  }

  /* ── Studio column ── */
  .vf-footer__studio {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--vf-s-4);
  }

  /* Logo asset: shopify_logo.svg at 32px height. SVG is 4:1; width follows automatically. */
  .vf-footer__logo {
    height: 32px;
    width: auto;
    display: block;
    align-self: flex-start;   /* pins to intrinsic 128px; prevents stretch centering */
  }

  .vf-footer__studio-desc {
    font-family: var(--vf-ff-body);
    font-weight: var(--vf-w-light);
    font-size: var(--vf-fs-body);
    line-height: var(--vf-lh-body);
    color: var(--vf-fg-3);
    /* Typographic measure (matches JSX). Same category as Material's 460px. */
    max-width: 280px;
    margin: 0;
  }

  /* ── Link columns ── */
  .vf-footer__col {
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
    gap: var(--vf-s-2);
  }

  /* 9px: navigation label chrome — deliberate exception to 11px body floor.
     Same register as Atelier metric labels and Material FIG. caption.
     Tracking: 0.28em (--vf-track-eyebrow); JSX 0.30em — token wins. */
  .vf-footer__col-title {
    font-family: var(--vf-ff-mono);
    font-size: 9px;
    font-weight: var(--vf-w-light);
    letter-spacing: var(--vf-track-eyebrow);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--vf-fg-3);
    margin-bottom: var(--vf-s-1);
  }

  .vf-footer__col-links {
    list-style: none;
    margin: 0;
    padding: 0;
  }

  .vf-footer__link {
    font-family: var(--vf-ff-body);
    font-weight: var(--vf-w-light);
    font-size: var(--vf-fs-body);
    /* line-height 2.2: deliberate literal — controls click-target spacing
       between links; no token exists in this range. Matches JSX exactly. */
    line-height: 2.2;
    color: var(--vf-fg-3);
    text-decoration: none;
    display: block;
    transition: color var(--vf-dur-fast) var(--vf-ease);
  }

  .vf-footer__link:hover {
    color: var(--vf-fg-1);
  }

  /* ── Region 3 · Bottom bar ── */
  .vf-footer__bottom {
    padding: var(--vf-s-4) var(--vf-grid-margin-d);
    border-top: var(--vf-hairline) solid var(--vf-border-2);
  }

  .vf-footer__bottom-inner {
    max-width: var(--vf-grid-max);
    margin: 0 auto;
    display: flex;
    justify-content: space-between;
    align-items: center;
    gap: var(--vf-s-5);
  }

  .vf-footer__social {
    display: flex;
    gap: var(--vf-s-4);
  }

  .vf-footer__social-link {
    color: var(--vf-fg-3);
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: color var(--vf-dur-fast) var(--vf-ease);
  }

  /* ↗ injected via CSS — approved unicode glyph (CLAUDE.md §3). Not in merchant content. */
  .vf-footer__social-link::after {
    content: " ↗";
    font-family: var(--vf-ff-mono);
    font-size: var(--vf-fs-mono-2);
  }

  /* Override vf-mono's colour so the parent anchor's transition drives hover. */
  .vf-footer__social-link .vf-mono {
    color: inherit;
  }

  .vf-footer__social-link:hover {
    color: var(--vf-fg-1);
  }

  /* ── Mobile ── */
  @media screen and (max-width: 749px) {
    .vf-footer__newsletter {
      padding: var(--vf-s-7) var(--vf-grid-margin-m);
    }

    .vf-footer__columns {
      padding: var(--vf-s-7) var(--vf-grid-margin-m);
    }

    .vf-footer__studio-desc {
      max-width: none;
    }

    .vf-footer__bottom {
      padding: var(--vf-s-4) var(--vf-grid-margin-m);
    }

    .vf-footer__bottom-inner {
      flex-direction: column;
      align-items: flex-start;
      gap: var(--vf-s-3);
    }
  }
{% endstyle %}

{% schema %}
{
  "name": "Voxel Forge · Footer",
  "tag": "section",
  "class": "shopify-section--vf-footer",
  "settings": [
    {
      "type": "header",
      "content": "Newsletter"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "id": "newsletter_headline_part_1",
      "label": "Newsletter headline (first line)",
      "default": "A quarterly note from"
    },
    {
